result.name: Genki Sushi

reviews.text: This outlet (not all) of Genki is ok. Good (not great) sushi at reasonable price. Beware some outlets' quality can vary a lot.

Genki sushi is a fast service sushi restaurant at the hk ferry terminal. I got excited about the technology and minimal human interaction. You get a ticket to get seated. Once you are seated you scan the QR code to place your order and you can place as many time. delivery is in carousel boats. Decent sushis and hot meals
Taste good, reasonable price

Worst service forever. 
1. You need to use your own phone, scan QR Code to order. Menu is also on your phone so it’s so hard to use even though I’m a teenager. 

2. You can place an order with maximum 8 stuffs only. That means if you want to order 9 things, you need to separate it into 2 orders.

3. No straw would be provided. 

4. No kaiten (rotating sushi) anymore, instead, a stupid “train” operating. For sure that’s just because of saving cost.

5. At the end, this is not Japanese operating. Trust me. Japanese would not offer that kind of inconvenient service to consumers.
Great variety of sushi at affordable prices. Very positive experience.
